    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-20T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-20T06:00:00-05:00" n="221"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Mutual Guarantee (Locarno)/485:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-20T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 20, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 20—10:35
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. My telegram No. 20, March 18, 5 p.m. I have ascertained from confidential
                    source that delegates assembled at London recognize merely formal character of
                    meetings yesterday and today except that Italy’s allegation of inability to
                    participate in any Rhineland patrol <pb facs="0343" n="263" xml:id="pg_263"/>
                    scheme pending lifting of sanctions will cause measures to be taken today to
                    lessen Italo-Abyssinian tension with a view to realistic settlement.</p>
                <p>Negotiations pending German referendum and French elections will probably be
                    characterized by denunciation and recrimination especially by Germans in the
                    interest of political expediency. Nevertheless, France and Great Britain will
                    take no action against Germany and German troops will not be withdrawn from the
                    Rhineland. Subsequent conversation will be lengthy due to the intention to work
                    out constructive program of the nature indicated by my telegram of March 18.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
